        <h2 id="verdict">Is Machined worth it in 2026? Final verdict</h2>
        <p><strong>For SEO consultants and agencies: yes, with caveats.</strong> The cluster engine is the most efficient mapping tool in the category. If you have editors who can polish output and a separate SERP-optimisation tool, $49/mo for 30 clusters is a steal.</p>

        <p><strong>For programmatic-SEO experiments: yes.</strong> Throw 200 articles at a niche, see what sticks, double down on winners. Volume-first plays favour Machined.</p>

        <p><strong>For business owners without editors: almost always no.</strong> Unedited Machined output rarely cracks the top 30. You'll either spend hours per article cleaning up or watch rankings sit flat. A done-for-you platform costs less in total and ships better content.</p>

